class RollConventionEnum(Enum):
    """
    The convention for determining the sequence of calculation period end
    dates.

    It is used in conjunction with a specified frequency and the regular
    period start date of a calculation period, e.g. semi-annual IMM roll
    dates.

    :cvar EOM: Rolls on month end dates irrespective of the length of
        the month and the previous roll day.
    :cvar FRN: Roll days are determined according to the FRN Convention
        or Eurodollar Convention as described in ISDA 2000 definitions.
    :cvar IMM: IMM Settlement Dates. The third Wednesday of the
        (delivery) month.
    :cvar IMMCAD: The last trading day/expiration day of the Canadian
        Derivatives Exchange (Bourse de Montreal Inc) Three-month
        Canadian Bankers' Acceptance Futures (Ticker Symbol BAX). The
        second London banking day prior to the third Wednesday of the
        contract month. If the determined day is a Bourse or bank
        holiday in Montreal or Toronto, the last trading day shall be
        the previous bank business day. Per Canadian Derivatives
        Exchange BAX contract specification.
    :cvar IMMAUD: The last trading day of the Sydney Futures Exchange 90
        Day Bank Accepted Bills Futures contract (see
        http://www.sfe.com.au/content/sfe/trading/con_specs.pdf). One
        Sydney business day preceding the second Friday of the relevant
        settlement month.
    :cvar IMMNZD: The last trading day of the Sydney Futures Exchange NZ
        90 Day Bank Bill Futures contract (see
        http://www.sfe.com.au/content/sfe/trading/con_specs.pdf). The
        first Wednesday after the ninth day of the relevant settlement
        month.
    :cvar SFE: Sydney Futures Exchange 90-Day Bank Accepted Bill Futures
        Settlement Dates. The second Friday of the (delivery) month.
    :cvar NONE: The roll convention is not required. For example, in the
        case of a daily calculation frequency.
    :cvar TBILL: 13-week and 26-week U.S. Treasury Bill Auction Dates.
        Each Monday except for U.S. (New York) holidays when it will
        occur on a Tuesday.
    :cvar VALUE_1: Rolls on the 1st day of the month.
    :cvar VALUE_2: Rolls on the 2nd day of the month.
    :cvar VALUE_3: Rolls on the 3rd day of the month.
    :cvar VALUE_4: Rolls on the 4th day of the month.
    :cvar VALUE_5: Rolls on the 4th day of the month.
    :cvar VALUE_6: Rolls on the 6th day of the month.
    :cvar VALUE_7: Rolls on the 7th day of the month.
    :cvar VALUE_8: Rolls on the 8th day of the month.
    :cvar VALUE_9: Rolls on the 9th day of the month.
    :cvar VALUE_10: Rolls on the 10th day of the month.
    :cvar VALUE_11: Rolls on the 11th day of the month.
    :cvar VALUE_12: Rolls on the 12th day of the month.
    :cvar VALUE_13: Rolls on the 13th day of the month.
    :cvar VALUE_14: Rolls on the 14th day of the month.
    :cvar VALUE_15: Rolls on the 15th day of the month.
    :cvar VALUE_16: Rolls on the 16th day of the month.
    :cvar VALUE_17: Rolls on the 17th day of the month.
    :cvar VALUE_18: Rolls on the 18th day of the month.
    :cvar VALUE_19: Rolls on the 19th day of the month.
    :cvar VALUE_20: Rolls on the 20th day of the month.
    :cvar VALUE_21: Rolls on the 21st day of the month.
    :cvar VALUE_22: Rolls on the 22nd day of the month.
    :cvar VALUE_23: Rolls on the 23rd day of the month.
    :cvar VALUE_24: Rolls on the 24th day of the month.
    :cvar VALUE_25: Rolls on the 25th day of the month.
    :cvar VALUE_26: Rolls on the 26th day of the month.
    :cvar VALUE_27: Rolls on the 27th day of the month.
    :cvar VALUE_28: Rolls on the 28th day of the month.
    :cvar VALUE_29: Rolls on the 29th day of the month.
    :cvar VALUE_30: Rolls on the 30th day of the month.
    :cvar MON: Rolling weekly on a Monday.
    :cvar TUE: Rolling weekly on a Tuesday.
    :cvar WED: Rolling weekly on a Wednesday.
    :cvar THU: Rolling weekly on a Thursday.
    :cvar FRI: Rolling weekly on a Friday.
    :cvar SAT: Rolling weekly on a Saturday.
    :cvar SUN: Rolling weekly on a Sunday.
    """

    EOM = "EOM"
    FRN = "FRN"
    IMM = "IMM"
    IMMCAD = "IMMCAD"
    IMMAUD = "IMMAUD"
    IMMNZD = "IMMNZD"
    SFE = "SFE"
    NONE = "NONE"
    TBILL = "TBILL"
