@dataclass(kw_only=True)
class DividendConditions:
    """
    A type describing the conditions governing the payment of dividends to
    the receiver of the equity return.

    With the exception of the dividend payout ratio, which is defined for
    each of the underlying components.

    :ivar dividend_reinvestment: Boolean element that defines whether
        the dividend will be reinvested or not.
    :ivar dividend_entitlement: Defines the date on which the receiver
        on the equity return is entitled to the dividend.
    :ivar dividend_amount:
    :ivar dividend_payment_date: Specifies when the dividend will be
        paid to the receiver of the equity return. Has the meaning as
        defined in the ISDA 2002 Equity Derivatives Definitions. Is not
        applicable in the case of a dividend reinvestment election.
    :ivar dividend_period_effective_date: Dividend period has the
        meaning as defined in the ISDA 2002 Equity Derivatives
        Definitions. This element specifies the date on which the
        dividend period will commence.
    :ivar dividend_period_end_date: Dividend period has the meaning as
        defined in the ISDA 2002 Equity Derivatives Definitions. This
        element specifies the date on which the dividend period will
        end. It includes a boolean attribute for defining whether this
        end date is included or excluded from the dividend period.
    :ivar dividend_period: Defines the First Period or the Second
        Period, as defined in the 2002 ISDA Equity Derivatives
        Definitions.
    :ivar extra_ordinary_dividends: Reference to the party which
        determines if dividends are extraordinary in relation to normal
        levels.
    :ivar excess_dividend_amount: Determination of Gross Cash Dividend
        per Share.
    :ivar currency: The currency in which an amount is denominated.
    :ivar determination_method: Specifies the method according to which
        an amount or a date is determined.
    :ivar currency_reference: Reference to a currency defined elsewhere
        in the document
    :ivar dividend_fx_trigger_date: Specifies the date on which the FX
        rate will be considered in the case of a Composite FX swap.
    :ivar interest_accruals_method: Defines the way in which interests
        are accrued: the applicable rate (fixed or floating reference)
        and the compounding method. FpML entity
    :ivar number_of_index_units: Defines the Number Of Index Units
        applicable to a Dividend.
    :ivar declared_cash_dividend_percentage: Declared Cash Dividend
        Percentage. A value expressed in percentage units i.e. 5 means
        5%.
    :ivar declared_cash_equivalent_dividend_percentage: Declared Cash
        Equivalent Dividend Percentage. A value expressed in percentage
        units i.e. 5 means 5%.
    :ivar non_cash_dividend_treatment: Defines treatment of Non-Cash
        Dividends.
    :ivar dividend_composition: Defines how the composition of Dividends
        is to be determined.
    :ivar special_dividends: Specifies the method according to which
        special dividends are determined.
    """

